track.descriptions: The true test of problem solving: when one realizes that time and memory aren't infinite.

primary_contest.description:
Starting on April 10th, HackerRank will launch their monthly qualifier. 20 days to look for the top 20 coders. There will be a total of 3 levels where you will compete to solve 5 programming problems that cover the following topics:
  • algorithms
  • single player game
  • multi-player game
  • Machine Learning

Each problem will get progressively harder as you near the end of the month. You'll have to 'unlock' each problem to view and solve the next problem for a chance to win cool prizes for the top hackers! There will be different requirements to advance to each level:

4/10 - 1st Level: 1st problem, solve completely to move on to the next level or wait 5 days

4/15 - 2nd Level: 2nd & 3rd problems, score at least 50% of the possible points on either problem or wait till 4/20

4/20 – 3rd Level: 4th & 5th problems unlock

4/30 – Contest ends
primary_contest.name: 20/20 Hack
